# ─── Mobile environment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
#   The full URL of the backend server, e.g. http://192.168.1.42:4000
#
#   IMPORTANT: "localhost" on a real iPhone refers to the iPhone itself, NOT
#   your Mac.  If you see "network request failure" errors, this is almost
#   certainly the problem.
#
#   Auto-detection (zero-config for development):
#     If this variable is NOT set, the app will try to auto-detect the Mac's
#     LAN IP from Expo's hostUri (the Metro bundler address).  This works
#     automatically in Expo Go when your Mac and iPhone are on the same Wi-Fi
#     network.  The Login screen and Record screen both show the resolved URL
#     so you can verify at a glance.
#
#   When to set it manually:
#     - Auto-detection fails (e.g. you are using a tunnel / ngrok).
#     - You are building a standalone app (Expo Go is not used).
#     - You want to point at a hosted / staging backend.
#
#   How to find your Mac's LAN IP:
#     System Settings → Wi-Fi → (i) next to your network → IP Address
#     or run: ipconfig getifaddr en0
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_PORT
#   Override the backend port used during auto-detection (default: 4000).
#   Only needed if you changed the PORT env var on the backend.

# Uncomment and set to your Mac's LAN IP when auto-detection is not available:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.42:4000

# Only needed if your backend runs on a non-standard port:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_PORT=4000
